<HL> Business Brief: Pamour Inc. </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<CO> T.PAM GYK </CO>
<IN> TNM </IN>
<TEXT>
   Pamour Inc., Toronto, said Giant Resources Ltd. of Australia plans to offer 10 Canadian dollars a share for the 5.8 million Pamour shares that it doesn't already own. 

   Giant Resources currently owns 51% of Pamour. 
The offer would have an indicated value of 58 million dollars (about $45.9 million). 
Pamour last traded at 8.25 dollars, up 1.50, when trading was halted yesterday on the Toronto Stock Exchange for reasons that weren't immediately clear. 

   Pamour is a holding company with interests in gold-mining companies, including a 42% stake in Toronto-based Giant Yellowknife Mines Ltd. Giant Resources is a gold-mining company. 

   Pamour executives weren't available for comment. 

</TEXT>
